         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper dual funds are evaluated to see if they provide the investor with a real economic service. They are also analyzed to establish guidelines for the answers to such questions as these: How should an investor decide which half of a dual fund to buy? Should he invest in dual funds at all? What portfolio policies should management adopt if it wants to treat each class of shareholder equally?</p>
